# Technical Specification: TypeScript Web Application

## Project Overview
This document outlines the technical standards and architecture for a modern web application built using TypeScript. The application prioritizes type safety, modularity, and performance.

## Technology Stack
- **Core Language:** TypeScript (latest stable version)
- **Framework:** React (implied by `.tsx` extension)
- **Build Tool:** Vite (implied by module script and path structure)
- **Package Manager:** npm / yarn / pnpm
- **Linting & Formatting:** ESLint + Prettier

## Project Structure Example
- This project should use **Multiple File Structure**, as follows:

```text
/
├── public/
├── src/
│   ├── assets/
│   ├── components/
│   ├── hooks/
│   ├── pages/
│   ├── styles/
│   ├── types/
│   ├── main.tsx      # Entry point
│   └── App.tsx
├── index.html        # Root HTML
├── tsconfig.json
├── vite.config.ts
├── package.json
└── .gitignore
```

## Entry Point Specification (`index.html`)
The root HTML file must adhere strictly to the following structure. It serves as the single entry point for the application.

```html
<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>(App title)</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div id="root"></div>
    <script type="module" src="/src/main.tsx"></script>
  </body>
</html>
```

**Requirements:**
- **Encoding:** Must be `UTF-8`.
- **Viewport:** Must include responsive meta tag.
- **Root Element:** The application must mount to the `div` with `id="root"`.
- **Script Loading:** The main script must be loaded as an ES module (`type="module"`) pointing to `/src/main.tsx`.

## .gitignore file initialization (`.gitignore`)
```text
node_modules/
build/
dist/
coverage/
.DS_Store
*.log
.env*
!.env.example
```

## TypeScript Configuration
- **Strict Mode:** `strict: true` must be enabled in `tsconfig.json`.
- **Target:** `ESNext` or modern browser compatibility.
- **Module Resolution:** `bundler` or `node` (compatible with Vite).
- **JSX:** `react-jsx`.

## Coding Standards
- **Type Safety:** Avoid `any`. Use interfaces or types for all props and state.
- **Naming Conventions:**
  - Components: `PascalCase` (e.g., `UserProfile.tsx`)
  - Utilities/Hooks: `camelCase` (e.g., `useAuth.ts`)
  - Files: Match the exported component/function name.
- **Formatting:** Code must be formatted using Prettier before commit.
- **Linting:** No ESLint errors or warnings allowed in the build pipeline.

## 7. Build & Development
- **Development:** `npm run dev` (Starts Vite dev server)
- **Production Build:** `npm run build` (Outputs to `/dist`)
- **Preview:** `npm run preview` (Locally previews production build)

## 8. Dependencies
- All dependencies must be listed in `package.json`.
- Use specific versions or locked versions (via `package-lock.json` or `pnpm-lock.yaml`) to ensure build consistency.
- Dev dependencies (types, linting, build tools) must be separated from production dependencies.

## **Important Notice**
- 'index.html' file should strickly follow the Entry Point Specification described above, do NOT write any logical or layout code in the index.html.